# Advanced Functional Programming with Elixir - Examples

## How to Use These Notebooks

1. Click a chapter link below to open the examples in Livebook  
2. Run code cells with `Ctrl+Enter` or the ▶ button  
3. Experiment freely — modify examples and see results immediately  
4. No setup required — everything runs in your browser  

## Interactive Chapters

- [Chapter 1: Build FunPark – Model Real-World Data](chap_01_funpark.livemd)  
  Define the park domain with rides, patrons, and fast passes

- [Chapter 2: Implement Domain-Specific Equality with Protocols](chap_02_eq.livemd)  
  Create flexible equality by implementing `Eq`

- [Chapter 3: Create Flexible Ordering with Protocols](chap_03_ord.livemd)  
  Express comparisons and sorting through `Ord`

- [Chapter 4: Combine with Monoids](chap_04_monoid.livemd)  
  Explore associative operations and identity elements

- [Chapter 5: Define Logic with Predicates](chap_05_predicate.livemd)  
  Build composable boolean conditions from simple parts

- [Chapter 6: Compose in Context with Monads](chap_06_monad.livemd)  
  Learn the fundamentals of sequencing with monads

- [Chapter 7: Access Shared Environment with Reader](chap_07_reader.livemd)  
  Thread configuration and context without clutter

- [Chapter 8: Manage Absence with Maybe](chap_08_maybe.livemd)  
  Model optional data safely, avoiding nulls

- [Chapter 9: Model Outcomes with Either](chap_09_either.livemd)  
  Represent success and failure explicitly

- [Chapter 10: Coordinate Tasks with Effect](chap_10_effect.livemd)  
  Combine async operations with error handling

